    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Driver Side Sliding Window Assembly</title>
        <para>The driver side window is an extruded aluminum framed sliding window. An optional driver side storm window
            is also available. The driver side sliding window assembly is secured in place with 9 mounting screws. To
            remove the standard driver window assembly:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the forward section of the driver side window to the rear. Locate the two frame
                mounting screws on the forward vertical extrusion. Loosen and remove the fasteners.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the two mounting screws on the bottom extrusion of the forward window section. Loosen
                and remove the mounting screws.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47003149" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003149.webp" filename="../figg47/g47003149.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 149. Vertical Frame Mounting Screws</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER WINDOW FORWARD VERTICAL FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER WINDOW VERTICAL FRAME MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">LOWER WINDOW FRAME MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">SLIDING WINDOW LOWER FRAME AND TRACK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide both window sections forward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the remaining two lower extrusion mounting screws at the rear bottom frame section.
                Loosen and remove the mounting screws.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the two screws fastening the rear vertical extrusion to the bus structure, loosen and
                remove.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47003150" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003150" filename="../figg47/g47003150.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 150. Upper Frame Mounting Screws</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVES WINDOW UPPER FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER WINDOW UPPER FRAME MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER WINDOW VERTICAL FRAME MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER WINDOW GLASS PANELS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the three mounting screws along the upper window frame attaching the window to the
                window header.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the mounting screws and remove the driver side sliding window assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
